1# Reserve Keywords 
	**Reserved word for data-types (8)
		byte, short, int, long, float, double, char, boolean
	**Reserved words for flow control (11)
		if, else, switch, case, default, while, do, for, break, continue, return	
	**Reserved words for modifiers (11)
		public, private, protected, final, abstract, static, synchronized, native, strinctfp, transists, volatile	
	**Reserved words for exception handeling (5)
		try, catch, finally, throw, throws	
	**class related keywords (7)
		class, interface, package, import, extends, implements, abstract	
	**object related keywords (4)
		new, instanceof, super, this
	**void -- if method won't return anything

2# java first program

3# command line argument 

4# Data-types with it's implicit and explicit type casting
   - size, capacity
   - 1.7 enhancement  
   - default values
   		- integral -> 0
   		- floating point -> 0.0
   		- boolean -> false
   		- reference type -> null
   		- char -> \u
   
